<p>Well, this has been sitting in my sandbox forever. Full disclosure: the dialogue at the very beginning is supposed to be in a Victorian English dialect. The reason I hadn't been uploading this was <em>because</em> I couldn't figure out for the life of me how to get that across without sounding idiotic. I have been asking for help (heavy help, involved help) for a while, but was unable to get it. Maybe this author post existing and asking for that will help out some. So far my ideas are to use a shit ton of synonyms.</p>
<p>Anyways, yeah. This <em>would</em> be the basis for a canon I wanted to launch if it weren't for the fact that I don't think I have the energy to keep writing for it. Also, no clue how this will be received. I imagine badly.</p>

