			<div class="content" id="post-content-3618466">
									

<p>+1</p>
<p>Great writing. I liked how you used text alignment to denote different speaking parties. I really liked how you described the girl's psychic/electro-kinetic abilities.</p>
<div class="collapsible-block">
<div class="collapsible-block-folded"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">+&nbsp;My&nbsp;interpretation</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded" style="display:none">
<div class="collapsible-block-unfolded-link"><a class="collapsible-block-link" href="javascript:;">-&nbsp;Hide</a></div>
<div class="collapsible-block-content">
<p>Something terrible is coming to Victorian Earth. Some anomalous beast with a thousand arms is coming to eat EVERYONE's soul. The Victorian scientists have found a &quot;Hail Mary&quot; solution, but they're not sure if it will work. Worst case, it will euthanize everyone on the planet, which would still be better than the alternative of being eaten by Beast Hands. Best case, everyone &quot;ascends&quot; to become one with the universe or somesuch, before the Beast can eat everyone. The Machine works by sending everyone to a sped-up version of reality. Essentially everyone on the planet will live out the next 100+ years in a simulated world, but doing so in the few moments before the Beast eats their souls. (Perhaps there's a cycle of death and reincarnation for everyone.) Their brains will accumulate 100s of years of memories and collapse into black holes, but their souls will break free and live on. They've tried it on two people, and neither of them were really conclusive.</p>
<p>I'm a little fuzzier on this part, but I believe that the character in the second part is EITHER one of the first two test subjects, OR some random girl on Earth AFTER they've turned the machine on. The machine has been running for at most a few mintutes, but for the people inside it's been 100s of years and the world has progressed. The girl is starting to reach enlightenment and fullfill that original goal of the machine. She can access the Spirit Plane. By touching her mom's brain, she was able to access the &quot;real&quot; world outside the simulation. Things are going super slow here, comparatively, and she sees the Beast trying to eat everyone's souls. Fortunately, the machine works, so, yay?</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

